26:39.681 --> 26:43.810
My point is, in reality,
it doesn't work the way you expect.

26:43.893 --> 26:47.147
When you stab somebody,
they're supposed to fall dead.

26:47.230 --> 26:48.189
They go, "Oh..."

26:48.273 --> 26:50.608
-And they fall dead, right?
-Right.

26:50.692 --> 26:54.279
In reality, when you stab somebody,
they lose blood pressure

26:54.362 --> 26:57.615
and they leak to death very slowly.

26:57.699 --> 27:00.410
So I was reluctant, I didn't enjoy it.

27:01.703 --> 27:03.204
Did you get that on tape?

27:03.872 --> 27:04.789
Yeah.

27:08.001 --> 27:09.961
You know, it all really goes back

27:10.045 --> 27:15.258
to my perceived inability
to communicate socially, sexually.

27:16.134 --> 27:19.721
I was scared to death of failing
in male-female relationships,

27:19.804 --> 27:22.057
even sitting down to talk to a young lady.

27:23.475 --> 27:25.143
I wanted to communicate.

27:25.685 --> 27:28.897
Ironically enough,
that's why I began picking people up.

27:28.980 --> 27:30.648
I pick a girl up

27:30.732 --> 27:33.068
and I'm going a little further each time.

27:33.151 --> 27:35.153
It's a daring kind of a thing.

27:35.236 --> 27:37.447
Like, first, there wasn't a gun.

27:37.530 --> 27:39.407
Then I'm driving along,

27:39.491 --> 27:42.452
